review_blob: 750ml bottle. chocolate coffee sweet aroma, very complex taste, vine-like. simply love it!brownish red, cloudy, medium sweetness, lightly bitter, lightly sour, long finish, soft carbonation, slick feel,
drunk many cans of this, not so bad for a such cheap beer, even more taste than m. lite. light corny, medium body, lively carbonation, thin feel,
Waterish. the most popular usa beer, what marketing does :) simply, theres nothing special in this one, it misses nice firm head, it misses hop taste.

Dark brown, middle caramel, a bit of smoke aroma. i wasnt impressed with this one (it simply doesnt have a taste  fullness which every good porter should have), but i didnt try a better porter in Slovakia, unfortunately
1 l bottle, package and picture on it is the nicest part of this one. simply this ones not 4 me. sourish aftertaste, grass, golden, hazy, medium body, lively carbonisation,
Unusual white bottle. you can taste alcohol in this one, but not too much as i expected, strong caramel and coffee taste, light co2, lot of sweetness (maybe a little too much for me)

very bitter, lightly sour, for me too much carbonized. it was much better some 5-7 years ago, nowdays is too bitter with longlasting bitterness afrertaste. Zagrebaka Pivovara (InBev) should learn from Lianka (brewer of Velebitsko Tamno) how to make a good porter.

i tried it drought, but i think it was mixed with water in Mali Medo (Tkalieva, Zagreb), light caramel taste, light sweetness, i dont know why they called it Extra Jako (means (Extra Strong) becouse theres no particular taste and no taste of alcohol at all.
not quite good as Velebitsko Tamno, but nice for refreshing purposes :-) light carbonated, light fruity taste.
medium body, creamy, soft carbonation, not so hard to find it in Croatia anymore, nice taste, not too much CO2, light caramelisation aftertaste. i think this is best Croatian beer. recommended.
i tried it in the bottle. very good beer; light caramel taste, it should be properly cold for real enjoyment.
i simply love this one. full taste but light to drink, with little bit of caramel. the price in Austria is under 1 what is for me best-buy beer.

Croatia doesnt have a lot of good beers, but this one is real disaster. i feel slight headache after 2 bottles of this, after 4, my head was 1 mile wide :-) taste is so - so, little bit corny, and lot of sour.
i bought it in some supermarket in Austria for 1. this beer is not a beer, its dom peringnon. fantastic!!
very nice one, tasty, and very drinkable :-) i bought it in austria, and found in 2 pubs in croatia. very good beer for amount of 2
